ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.

ElementDescription: Sex of subject at birth
Notes: M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: 1. Arranges toys or other items in rows or patterns?
Notes: 1 = Never or rarely; 2 = One or more times daily; 3 = 15 or more times daily; 4 = 30 or more times daily

ElementDescription: 2. Repetitively fiddle with toys or other items?
Notes: 1 = Never or rarely; 2 = One or more times daily; 3 = 15 or more times daily; 4 = 30 or more times daily

ElementDescription: 3. Spin him/herself around and around?
Notes: 1 = Never or rarely; 2 = One or more times daily; 3 = 15 or more times daily; 4 = 30 or more times daily

ElementDescription: "4. Rock backwards and forwards, or side to side, wither when sitting or when standing?"
Notes: 1 = Never or rarely; 2 = One or more times daily; 3 = 15 or more times daily; 4 = 30 or more times daily

ElementDescription: 5. Pace or move around repetitively?
Notes: 1 = Never or rarely; 2 = One or more times daily; 3 = 15 or more times daily; 4 = 30 or more times daily

ElementDescription: 6. Make repetitive hand and/or finger movements?
Notes: 1 = Never or rarely; 2 = One or more times daily; 3 = 15 or more times daily; 4 = 30 or more times daily

ElementDescription: 7. Have a fascination with specific objects?
Notes: 1 = Never or rarely; 2 = Mild or occasional; 3 = Marked or notable

ElementDescription: 8. Like to look at objects from particular or unusual angles?
Notes: 1 = Never or rarely; 2 = Mild or occasional; 3 = Marked or notable

ElementDescription: 9. Have a special interest in the smell of people or objects?
Notes: 1 = Never or rarely; 2 = Mild or occasional; 3 = Marked or notable

ElementDescription: 10. Have a special interest in the feel of different surfaces
Notes: 1 = Never or rarely; 2 = Mild or occasional; 3 = Marked or notable

ElementDescription: 11. Have any special objects he/she likes to carry around?
Notes: 1 = Never or rarely; 2 = Mild or occasional; 3 = Marked or notable

ElementDescription: 12. Collect or hoard items of any sort?
Notes: 1 = Never or rarely; 2 = Mild or occasional; 3 = Marked or notable

ElementDescription: 13. Insist on things at home remaining the same?
Notes: 1 = Never or rarely; 2 = Mild or occasional; 3 = Marked or notable

ElementDescription: 14. Get upset about minor chages to objects?
Notes: 1 = Never or rarely; 2 = Mild or occasional; 3 = Marked or notable

ElementDescription: 15. Insist that aspects of daily routine must remain the same?
Notes: 1 = Never or rarely; 2 = Mild or occasional; 3 = Marked or notable

ElementDescription: 16. Insist on doing things in a certain way or redoing things until they are just right?
Notes: 1 = Never or rarely; 2 = Mild or occasional; 3 = Marked or notable

ElementDescription: "17. Play the same music, game or video, or read the same book repeatedly?"
Notes: 1 = Never or rarely; 2 = Mild or occasional; 3 = Marked or notable

ElementDescription: 18. Insist on wearing the same clothes or refuse to wear new clothes?
Notes: 1 = Never or rarely; 2 = Mild or occasional; 3 = Marked or notable

ElementDescription: "19. Insist on eating the same foods, or a very small range of foods, at every meal?"
Notes: 1 = Never or rarely; 2 = Mild or occasional; 3 = Marked or notable

ElementDescription: 20. What sort of activity will your child choose if they are left to occupy themselves.
Notes: 1 = A range of different and flexible self-chosen activities; 2 = Some varied and flexible interests but commonly chooses the same activities; 3 = Almost always chooses from a restricted range of repetitive activities

ElementDescription: Total Repetitive Behaviors Score
Factor 1 - Repetitive Motor Movements Score
Factor 2 - Rigidity/Adherence to Routine Score
Factor 3 - Proccupation with Restricted Patterns of Interest Score
Factor 4 - Unusual Sensory Interest Score
Factor 1 - Motor/Sensory Behaviors
Factor 2 - Rigidity/Routines/Preoccupation with Restricted Interests
